# Runtime Layer Rules

The runtime layer handles networking, data persistence, and OS-level services. It sits between engine and app layers.

## Import Restrictions
- NEVER import from `apps/` or `presentation/`
- OK to import from `engine/` packages
- OK to import from `shared/avrai_core`

## Standards
- Use `developer.log()` from `dart:developer`, never `print()`
- All mesh communication must use `AnonymousCommunicationProtocol` (not `AdvancedAICommunication`)
- Never share raw personality data over mesh -- only anonymized gradients (DP-protected)
- Never access message content from chat services for ML features -- only metadata
- Use `AtomicClockService` timestamps for time-sensitive data
